---
/**
 * The cost of guessing — why first-attempt accuracy matters. Sits inside the
 * scroll stage, so the constellation drifts behind it while these numbers land.
 */
---

<section class="problem stage-panel section" id="problem">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">The cost of guessing</p>
      <h2 class="title">
        Guessing is expensive. Repeating it is worse.
      </h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Most color-matching tools start from a generic model and spend months
        correcting toward your factory — after you've paid for new hardware.
        Color Brain starts from the recipes your factory already proved, on day
        one.
      </p>
    </div>
    <dl class="problem__readouts reveal">
      <div>
        <span class="problem__index">01 / Attempts</span>
        <dt class="readout__value">4–6</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">attempts on average to approve a new color</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="problem__index">02 / Failure</span>
        <dt class="readout__value">50%</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">of first attempts miss the target</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="problem__index">03 / Cost</span>
        <dt class="readout__value">$500–2K</dt>
        <dd class="readout__label">typical cost per failed attempt</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    overflow: hidden;
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at 86% 18%, rgba(224, 108, 117, 0.07), transparent 28rem),
      var(--surface);
  }

  .problem::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: -10rem;
    right: 7vw;
    width: 28rem;
    height: 28rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(224, 108, 117, 0.09);
    border-radius: 50%;
    box-shadow:
      0 0 0 5rem rgba(224, 108, 117, 0.018),
      0 0 0 10rem rgba(224, 108, 117, 0.012);
  }

  .problem .container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .problem__readouts {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    margin-top: 4rem;
    border-block: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--line);
  }

  .problem__readouts > div {
    min-height: 13rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding: 1.6rem;
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .problem__index {
    margin-bottom: auto;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.61rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fail);
  }

  .problem__readouts dd {
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
